JOHANNESBURG &#8211; Moody&#8217;s said on Tuesday it will not issue a sovereign credit rating decision on South Africa this Friday, as previously planned, but will do so after a review that could take 30 to 90 days.Moody&#8217;s announced on Monday that it had placed South Africa on a review for a downgrade after a cabinet reshuffle that saw a respected former finance minister dismissed from his post.Moody&#8217;s currently has South Africa&#8217;s sovereign at two notches above non-investment grade at Baa2.